quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
31,1,"Alif. Lam. Mim."
31,2,"These are the verses of the Wise Book, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
31,3,"a guidance and mercy for the doers of good, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
31,4,"who establish Prayer and pay Zakah, and have firm faith in the Hereafter. {1}",footnotes:1:It does not mean that the righteous people bear only these three qualities. By using the common epithet of righteous for them
31,5,"It is they who are on true guidance from their Lord, and it is they who shall prosper. {1}",footnotes:1:At the time when these verses were sent down
31,6,"There are some human beings {1} who purchase an enchanting diversion {2} in order to lead people away from the way of Allah without having any knowledge, {3} who hold the call to the Way of Allah to ridicule. {4} A humiliating chastisement awaits them. {5}",footnotes:1:That is
31,7,"When Our verses are recited to such a person, he arrogantly turns away, as though he had not heard them, or as though there was a deafness in his ears. So announce to him the tidings of a grievous chastisement."
31,8,"Surely those who believe and do good deeds shall have Gardens of Bliss. {1}",footnotes:1:Instead of saying “There are blessings of Paradise (Gardens) for them
31,9,"They shall abide in them forever. This is Allah's promise that shall come true. He is the Most Powerful, the Most Wise. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
31,10,"He {1} created the heavens without any pillars visible to you {2} and He placed mountains in the earth as pegs lest it should turn topsy turvy with you, {3} and He dispersed all kinds of animals over the earth, and sent down water from the sky causing all kinds of excellent plants to grow on it.",footnotes:1:After the above introductory sentence
31,11,"Such is Allah's creation. Show me, then, what any others, apart from Allah, have created. {1} Nay, the fact is that the wrong-doers are in manifest error. {2}",footnotes:1:“Those other than” “the beings whom you have set up as your deities
